				 S. Kumars arm eyes fresh funds
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, Nov. 28: Textile company S. Kumars Nationwide Ltd is planning private equity investments in demerged entity Reid amp; Taylor (India) Ltd.																								It also intends to make an initial public offer for Reid amp; Taylor. The decision to demerge the Reid amp; Taylor division which focuses on the high end of the textile business was taken at a board meeting of S. Kumars Nationwide on Tuesday. 																								In a notice sent to the stock exchanges, S. Kumars said the subsidiarisation of the Reid amp; Taylor division was done to ensure a greater focus on the luxury textiles and premium garment businesses.																								Apart from Reid amp; Taylor, the other brands in the companys portfolio include S. Kumars, Carmichael House and Belmonte. Reid amp; Taylor was launched in the country more than 8 years ago and the brand now has a strong presence in the premium segment. Recent reports said the company had plans to open more outlets both in India and abroad.
